 unlock your screen when locking your screen for the first time.\n*Install drivers for the Video Acceleration API to improve the display of videos on many graphics cards.\n|-\n| {{Version | o | 3.7}}<ref name=\"version3.7\">{{cite web |url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_3.7/index.en.html |title=Tails 3.7 is out |date=2018-05-09 |accessdate=2018-05-09 }}</ref>\n| {{dts|2018-05-09}}<ref name=\"version3.7\" />\n|\n|-\n| {{Version | o | 3.8}}<ref name=\"version3.8\">{{cite web |url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_3.8/index.en.html |title=Tails 3.8 is out |date=2018-06-26 |accessdate=2018-07-17 }}</ref><ref>[https://distrowatch.com/weekly.php?issue=20180702#released DistroWatch Weekly, Issue 770, 2 July 2018]</ref>\n| {{dts|2018-06-26}}<ref name=\"version3.8\" />\n|\n|-\n| {{Version | o | 3.9}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_3.9/index.en.html|title=Tails - Tails 3.9 is out|website=tails.boum.org|access-date=2018-09-06}}</ref><ref name=\"tails_calendar\">{{cite web |url=https://tails.boum.org/contribute/calendar/ |title=Tails - Calendar |date=2018-07-17 |accessdate=2018-07-17 }}</ref>\n| {{dts|2018-09-05}}<ref name=\"tails_calendar\" />\n|\n*Firefox 60.2, major release; will include VeraCrypt support and major Additional Software Packages improvements.<ref name=\"tails_calendar\" />\n|-\n|{{Version | o | 3.9.1}}<ref name=\"version3.9\">{{Cite web|url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_3.9.1/index.en.html|title=Tails - Release notes|website=tails.boum.org|access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref>\n|October 3, 2018<ref name=\"version3.9\" />\n|\n* Update ''Tor Browser'' to 8.0.2.  This fixes 2 critical security vulnerabilities in JavaScript in ''Firefox''.\n* Update ''Thunderbird'' to fix these same vulnerabilities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_3.9.1/index.en.html|title=Tails - Tails 3.9.1 is out|website=tails.boum.org|access-date=2018-10-06}}</ref>\n|-\n|{{Version | o | 3.10.1}}<ref name=\"version3.10\">{{Cite web|url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_3.10.1/index.en.html|title=Tails 3.10.1 is out |website=tails.boum.org|access-date=2018-10-28}}</ref>\n|October 23, 2018\n|\n* Hide the '''PIM''' option when unlocking ''VeraCrypt'' volumes because ''PIM'' won't be supported until Tails 4.0. (#16031)\n* Rename the buttons in the confirmation dialog of ''Tails Installer'' to '''Install''' (or '''Upgrade''') and '''Cancel''' to be less confusing. (#11501)\n* Update ''Linux'' to 4.8.\n* Update ''Tor Browser'' to 8.0.3.\n* Update ''Thunderbird'' to 60.2.1.\n|-\n|{{Version | o | 4.0}}<ref name=\"version4.0\">{{Cite web|url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_4.0/index.en.html|title=Tails 4.0 is out |website=tails.boum.org|access-date=2019-11-19}}</ref>\n|October 22, 2019<ref name=\"version4.0\" />\n|\n* Replace KeePassX with KeePassXC\n* Update ''Linux'' to 5.3.2\n* Update ''OnionShare'' to 1.3.2\n* Update ''Tor Browser'' to 9.0<ref name=\"version4.0\" />\n|-\n|{{Version | o | 4.1}}<ref name=\"version4.1\">{{Cite web|url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_4.1/index.en.html|title=Tails 4.1 is out |website=tails.boum.org|access-date=2019-11-30}}</ref>\n|December 3, 2019<ref name=\"version4.1\" />\n|\n|-\n|{{Version | o | 4.1.1}}<ref name=\"version4.1.1\">{{Cite web|url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_4.1.1/index.en.html|title=Tails 4.1.1 is out |website=tails.boum.org|access-date=2019-11-30}}</ref>\n|December 17, 2019<ref name=\"version4.1.1\" />\n|\n|-\n|{{Version | o | 4.2}}<ref name=\"version4.2\">{{Cite web|url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_4.2/index.en.html|title=Tails 4.2 is out |website=tails.boum.org|access-date=2012-01-07}}</ref>\n|January 7, 2020<ref name=\"version4.2\" />\n|\n* Update Tor Browser to 9.0.3\n* Update Thunderbird to 68.3.0\n* Update Linux to 5.3.15<ref name=\"version4.2\" />\n|-\n|{{Version | c | 4.3}}<ref name=\"version4.3\">{{Cite web|url=https://tails.boum.org/contribute/calendar/|title=Tails - Calendar |website=tails.boum.org|access-date=2012-01-07}}</ref>\n|February 11, 2020<ref name=\"version4.3\" />\n|\n* Updated {{em|Tor Browser}} to 9.0.5\n* Updated {{em|Thunderbird}} to 68.4.1\n* Updated {{em|Linux Kernel}} to 5.4.13\n* Updated {{em|Tor}} to 0.4.2.6\n* Updated {{em|Virtualbox Guest Additions}} to 6.1.2\n|-\n! Version\n! Release date\n! class=\"unsortable\"| Notes\n|}\n\n==In mainstream media==\nOn 3 July 2014, German public television channel ''[[Das Erste]]'' reported that the [[NSA]]'s [[XKeyscore]] surveillance system contains definitions that match persons who search for Tails using a search engine or visit the Tails website. A [[Comment (computer programming)|comment]] in XKeyscore's source code calls Tails \"a [[Communications security|comsec]] mechanism advocated by [[Extremism|extremists]] on extremist forums\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://daserste.ndr.de/panorama/aktuell/NSA-targets-the-privacy-conscious,nsa230.html|author=[[Jacob Appelbaum]], A. Gibson, J. Goetz, V. Kabisch, L. Kampf, L. Ryge|title=NSA targets the privacy-conscious|publisher=DasErste.de |date=3 Jul 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.schneier.com/blog/archives/2014/07/nsa_targets_pri.html|title=NSA Targets Privacy Conscious for Surveillance|author=[[Bruce Schneier]]|work=Schneier on Security|date=3 Jul 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 December 2014, ''[[Der Spiegel]]'' published slides from an internal [[NSA]] presentation dating to June 2012 in which the NSA deemed Tails on its own as a \"major threat\" to its mission, and when used in conjunction with other privacy tools such as [[Off-the-Record Messaging|OTR]], Cspace, [[RedPhone]], and [[TrueCrypt]] was ranked as \"catastrophic,\" leading to a \"near-total loss/lack of insight to target communications, presence...\"<ref name=\"spiegel1\" /><ref name=\"spiegel2\" />\n\n== Tails partners ==\nOrganizations, companies and individuals that provide financial support to Tails through grants or donations are recognized as \"partners\",<ref>{{cite web |title=Tails: Partners |url=https://tails.boum.org/partners/become/ |accessdate=7 June 2019}}</ref> and have included:\n\n* [https://handshakefoundation.org Handshake Foundation]\n* [https://www.opentech.fund/ Open Technology Fund]\n* [[DuckDuckGo]]\n* [https://uk.lush.com/article/digital-fund-one-year-later Lush]\n* [[I2P]]\n* [[The Tor Project, Inc|Tor]]\n\n== See also ==\n{{Div col|colwidth=20em}}\n* [[Crypto-anarchism]]\n* [[Dark web]]\n* [[Deep web]]\n* [[Freedom of information]]\n* [[GlobaLeaks]]\n* [[GNU Privacy Guard]]\n* [[I2P]]\n* [[Internet censorship]]\n* [[Internet privacy]]\n* [[Off-the-Record Messaging]]\n* [[Proxy server]]\n* [[Security-focused operating system]]s\n* [[Tor (anonymity network)]]\n* [[Tor2web]]\n* [[Whonix]]\n{{div col end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"spiegel2\">{{cite magazine|title=Presentation from the SIGDEV Conference 2012 explaining which encryption protocols and techniques can be attacked and which not|url=http://www.spiegel.de/media/media-35535.pdf|magazine=Der Spiegel|accessdate=23 Jan 2015|format=PDF|date=28 Dec 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"spiegel1\">{{cite news|author=SPIEGEL Staff|title=Prying Eyes: Inside the NSA's War on Internet Security|url=http://www.spiegel.de/international/germany/inside-the-nsa-s-war-on-internet-security-a-1010361.html|newspaper=Der Spiegel|accessdate=23 Jan 2015|date=28 Dec 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"h\">{{citation |url=http://www.h-online.com/open/news/item/Tails-0-11-incognito-live-system-released-1563498.html |title=Tails 0.11 incognito live system released |first= |last= |work=[[The H]] |date=30 Apr 2012 |accessdate=12 Aug 2012 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"lj\">{{citation |url=http://www.linuxjournal.com/content/tails-projects-amnesic-incognito-live-system-tails |title=The Tails Project's The Amnesic Incognito Live System (Tails) |first=James |last=Gray |work=[[Linux Journal]] |date=16 Sep 2011 |accessdate=12 Aug 2012 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"lwn\">{{citation |url=https://lwn.net/Articles/440279/ |title=The Amnesic Incognito Live System: A live CD for anonymity |first=Koen |last=Vervloesem |work=[[LWN.net]] |date=27 Apr 2011 |accessdate=12 Aug 2012 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"tc\">{{citation |language=German |url=http://www.tecchannel.de/sicherheit/news/2038771/tails_0101_the_amnesic_incognito_live_system/ |title=Anonym im Netz |trans-title=Anonymous on the Net |first= |last= |work=[[TecChannel]] |date=6 Feb 2012 |accessdate=12 Aug 2012 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|The Amnesic Incognito Live System}}\n* {{Official website|https://tails.boum.org}}\n* [https://www.torproject.org/projects/projects.html.en Tails] at Tor project website\n* [https://tails.boum.org/support/known_issues/index.en.html Tails - Known issues]\n* [https://deeponion.org/community/threads/tails-deeponion-partnership-soon-to-start.39854/ Tails] at DeepOnion Website\n* {{distrowatch|tails|NAME=Tails}}\n\n{{Tor project}}\n{{Linux distributions}}\n{{Portal bar|Anarchism|Free and open-source software|Freedom of speech|Linux}}\n\n{{Use MDY dates|date=August 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Amnesic Incognito}}\n[[Category:Anonymity networks]]\n[[Category:Debian-based distributions]]\n[[Category:Free security software]]\n[[Category:I2P]]\n[[Category:Operating system distributions bootable from read-only media]]\n[[Category:Privacy software]]\n[[Category:Tor (anonymity network)]]\n", "name_user": "Thorwald", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePersistency:\"doesn't\" -> \"does not\" + \"shouldn't\" -> \"should not\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tails_(operating_system)"}
